What makes a word a piece of E-literature?
E-literature refers to electronic literature/writing. This means any writing or storytelling which occurs digitally, and which at least
somewhat relies on its digital format to sustain its audience. Including but not limited to interactive fiction, choose your own adventure 
narratives, and hyperlinks.

Of the key examples above, which did you like most and why?
There was little to no time for me to view/read any of the texts besides Shade, and for this exact reason, I can definitely say it's
my favourite. The concept was intriguing, and I enjoyed the challenge of not knowing exactly what I was supposed to do. The frustrations
of having no instructions for how I was supposed to achieve my goal, a very specific goal, was reminiscent of video games. I've always
thought that the kind of engagement created between a reader (or I suppose a 'player') and these kinds of interactive texts is something 
that cannot be replicated in standard fiction. The immersion of Shade really hooked me, and I loved trying to figure out the goal behind 
these (I assume) intentional feelings of frustration, isolation, and the illusion of control.

